Interface IPreferences

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AutoPreferences

    public interface IPreferences
    An interface for a system for accessing a preferences store.

    2016-02-17
    Author:
    Ethan Ruffing

      • put

        void put(String key,
         Object value)
        Stores any object in the preferences, overwriting any identically-named properties.

        Note: Do not abuse this method. Many backends are not intended for storing large data chunks and can be severely inhibited by doing so.

        Parameters:
        key - The key to store the object under.
        value - The object to store.

      • getBoolean

        boolean getBoolean(String key,
                   boolean def)
        Reads the stored value for an boolean preference.
        Parameters:
        key - The key that the preference is stored under.
        def - The default value to return if a setting is not found for the given key.
        Returns:
        The value stored for the preference, or the default value on failure.
